column5: This questionnaire is designed to assess patients  satisfaction as it relates to care received during their stay at this health facility. The information obtained would be confidential and used for monitoring and improvement plan in care services only.
column6: Would you like to provide us with the needed details? (Za ku so Ku Samar  mana da cikakkun bayani da ake bukata)
column10: In which state are you conducting this interview? (A wace jaha kuke yin interview din?)
column11: What is the name of this health facility (Minene sunan wannan asibiti)
column12: What is the interviewer's name (Minene sunan interviewer)
column13: The following questions collect information on socio-demographic characteristics of the respondent.
column14: A1. What is your name (Menene sunan ki?)
column15: A2. Patient's hospital ID (Lambar shaidar asibiti ta marar lafiya)
column16: A3i. How long have you been living with Fistula? (Tun yaushe kike zaune da yoyon fitsari?)
column17: A3ii. How did you develop the Fistula? (Yaya aka yi kika kamu da yoyon fitsari?)
column21: A4i. How old were you at last birthday? (Shikaran ki nawa?)
column22: A4ii. How old were you at your first pregnancy? (Shikaran ki nawa a lokacin cikin ki na farko?)
column23: A5i. What is your phone number (Minene Lambar wayar ki?)
column24: A5ii. Who has the phone number (Wana ke da Lambar wayar?)
column25: A5iii. Please, specify other (Idan wasu, saka)
column26: A5iv. Alternative phone number (Madadin lambar wayar)
column27: A5v. Who has the phone number (Wana ke da Lambar wayar?)
column28: A5vi. Please, specify other (Idan wasu, saka)
column29: A6i. What your state of residence ? (Menene Jihar zama)
column32: A6ii. Which of the LGAs in the state mentioned? (Wace karamar hukuma Ka ki?)
column33: A6iii. Which Community are you from? (Wane yanki Ka ki?)
column34: A7i.Were you married before the fistula occurred? (Kina de aure kafin yoyon fitsari ya sameki?)
column36: A8i. What is your highest level of education? (Menene matin (matsayin) illimin ki?)
column38: A9i. What is your Occupation (Menene Sana'a ki?)
column39: A9ii. If others, please state your occupation (Idan wasu, da fatan za'a bayyana Sana'arki)
column40: A9iii. Please specify your average monthly income (Saka matsakaicin kudin shigarki na wata-wata)
column41: A10i. Have you had any fistula surgery done before? (Shin an yi miki tiyatar yoyon fitsari a baya?)
column42: A10ii. If Yes, how many surgery have you had in the past? (Idan Ee, tiyata nawa aka yi muku a baya?)
column43: A11i. Who told you about the Fistula repair services? (Waya ba ki labarin aikin gyaran yoyon fitsari?)
column44: A11ii. Please, specify other (Idan wasu, saka)
column45: A12i. How did you get to the facility (Taya kika kawo kan ki asibiti)
column46: A12ii. Please specify other means of transport (Da fatan za'a saka wasu hanyoyin sufuri)
column47: A13i. Who consented to this repair apart from you? (Waya yarda da wannan gyaran banda ke?)
column49: A14i. How long did you stay in the facility before the surgery was done? (Tsawon wane lokaci kika zauna a asibiti kafin a yi tiyatar?)
column50: A14ii. After the surgery, how long did you stay in the facility (hospital) before discharge? (Baya tiyata, tsawon kwanaki nawa kika zauna a asibiti kafin sallama?)
column51: A15i. Are you completely healed now? (Kin warke gaba daya?)
column52: A15ii. If no, What other challenges relating with the surgery are you still feeling? (Idan a'a, wadanne kalubale(matsala) da suka shafi aikin tiyata kike ji har yanzu?)
column53: A16i. How much did you pay for this surgery? (Nawa kika biya a wannan tiyatar?)
column54: A16ii. Were you asked to bring any item before the surgery could be performed? (An umarce ki ki kawo wani abu kafin a yi aikin tiyatar?)
column55: A16iii. If yes, what item(s) did you bring? (Idan Eh, wadanne kayayyaki aka ce ki kawo?)
column56: A17i. Do you know other woman/women who might need this care in your community? (Shin kin san wasu mata wadanda za SU iya bakatar wannan kulawa a garinku?)
column57: A17ii.  If yes, will you like the person to be mobilized? (Idan Eh, za ki iya ba da shawarar wannan aiki din)
column58: A17iii. If yes, kindly provide us with the contact (Idan eh, da fatan za a ba mu lambar sadarwa)
column59: A18i. Are you planning to have more children in the future? (Shin kuna shirin samun ƙarin yara nan gaba?)
column62: A18iv. If No, why not?
column63: A19i. Is the patient physically challenged? (Shin mai haƙuri yana da ƙalubalen jiki?)
column64: A19ii. If yes, state challenge(s) (Idan eh, ƙalubalen jiha)
column65: Section B: I am going to read some things people say about medical care. Please listen to each one carefully, keeping in mind the medical care you received from this facility. We are interested in your feelings, good and bad about the medical care you have received. Please note that the “I” and “me” in the statements below refer to you as the recipient of the services. State "TRUE or FALSE" in agreement with each of the following statements?
column66: B1. During medical care, I am well examined and treated. (In na je neman magani, suna mai da hankali su duba komai)
column67: B2. I have doubts about the ability of the doctors who treat me. (Ina da shakku game da kwarerar likitocin da suke kula da ni)
column68: B3. Doctors did not address my personal concerns. (Likitoci suna aiki kamar kasuwanci kuma ba su nuna min kyakkyawar alaka ba)

column72: B7. Doctor/healthcare provider usually spends a lot of time with me. (Likita/ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya yawanci suna ciyar da lokaci mai yawa tare da ni.)
column73: B8. I have easy access to the doctor whenever needed. (Ina samun sauƙin samun likita lokacin da nake buƙata.)
column74: * B9. I have to wait long to consult the doctor. (Dole ne in jira tsawon lokaci don tuntubar likita)
